name: | Anguish, The World In Between |
description:
| Anguish |
|"The thought of doing it haunts me every second."- said the journal. As it should haunt you too. You'll never know how sweet something you haven't done and felt is. I tend to close my eyes as I drink, the act is physically reckless, the sweet, fine edge between joy and struggle. Though I accepted the fact that no matter what happens, whenever they ask me if I knew anything about the accident, I'd say no, I still feel like a traitor. Yet I'll take a shower, smile gently facing the mirror, put some nice clothes on and head out for a walk to forget that those shadows ever existed.
